780
00:31:10,869 --> 00:31:13,828
Sometimes, all it takes
is the right person

781
00:31:13,872 --> 00:31:15,482
to get you out.

782
00:31:15,525 --> 00:31:17,310
After all...

783
00:31:17,353 --> 00:31:18,789
[chuckles]

784
00:31:18,833 --> 00:31:20,008
...we both have needs.

785
00:31:21,357 --> 00:31:23,098
Another time.

786
00:31:23,142 --> 00:31:25,840
Hell, I'd be the luckiest
guy in the world,

787
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:27,320
but I'm in love with Chloe.

788
00:31:28,843 --> 00:31:30,236
Sorry.

789
00:31:33,979 --> 00:31:37,678
ELLA: I know we knew
what was on this video,

790
00:31:37,721 --> 00:31:41,638
yet somehow actually seeing
Myles' fake-fake leg--

791
00:31:41,682 --> 00:31:43,597
so much grosser.
Great.

792
00:31:43,640 --> 00:31:44,772
LUCIFER:
The man's an embarrassment

793
00:31:44,815 --> 00:31:46,643
to both dance and prosthetics.

794
00:31:46,687 --> 00:31:48,341
Well, we're just lucky
that cyber could retrieve this

795
00:31:48,384 --> 00:31:50,038
from Reina's computer.

796
00:31:50,082 --> 00:31:52,084
Dan, is there any way to tell
who made this from the footage?

797
00:31:52,127 --> 00:31:53,999
Nothing, no voice.
Not even a measly cough.

798
00:31:54,042 --> 00:31:55,783
Whoever did this was
pretty damn careful.

799
00:31:55,826 --> 00:31:57,567
Yeah, we're still waiting
for DNA results

800
00:31:57,611 --> 00:31:59,047
from the computer's keyboard,

801
00:31:59,091 --> 00:32:01,702
but if the killer wore gloves,
I mean, we're out of luck.

802
00:32:01,745 --> 00:32:03,922
[phone vibrating]

803
00:32:07,273 --> 00:32:08,709
[quietly]:
It's Pierce.

804
00:32:08,752 --> 00:32:10,885
[phone continues vibrating]

805
00:32:10,929 --> 00:32:12,669
Well, someone needs
to hit "ignore."

806
00:32:12,713 --> 00:32:13,932
We'll get it.

807
00:32:17,022 --> 00:32:17,979
Hey, Pierce, what's up?

808
00:32:18,023 --> 00:32:19,285
PIERCE:
Chloe, hi.

809
00:32:19,328 --> 00:32:20,982
Listen, I realize that
lemon bars and flowers

810
00:32:21,026 --> 00:32:22,244
aren't gonna cut it.

811
00:32:22,288 --> 00:32:23,767
I think I figured out a way
to prove to you

812
00:32:23,811 --> 00:32:25,291
you can trust me.

813
00:32:25,334 --> 00:32:27,641
Can you meet me at my place
for dinner tonight? 8:00?

814
00:32:27,684 --> 00:32:28,903
Eh, I don't know.

815
00:32:28,947 --> 00:32:30,122
Chloe, please.

816
00:32:30,165 --> 00:32:31,471
Listen, if you don't want
to see me after,

817
00:32:31,514 --> 00:32:33,777
I promise I will never
bother you again.

818
00:32:33,821 --> 00:32:36,780
Just... just come over.

819
00:32:36,824 --> 00:32:37,999
You gotta eat, right?

820
00:32:38,043 --> 00:32:41,307
Okay. Yeah, I can do dinner.

821
00:32:41,350 --> 00:32:43,570
Great. I'll see you then.

822
00:32:43,613 --> 00:32:45,137
LUCIFER:
Detective.
Hmm?

823
00:32:45,180 --> 00:32:47,704
I couldn't help but overhear
a part of your call

824
00:32:47,748 --> 00:32:49,576
and I understand
that you're torn,

825
00:32:49,619 --> 00:32:51,230
but before
you make a decision

826
00:32:51,273 --> 00:32:52,927
about Pierce
I'd like the chance

827
00:32:52,971 --> 00:32:54,842
to express some thoughts
to you, as well.

828
00:32:54,885 --> 00:32:57,018
Okay. Go ahead.

829
00:32:57,062 --> 00:32:59,760
Right, well, I...

830
00:33:01,414 --> 00:33:04,025
Actually, can we do this
in private?

831
00:33:04,069 --> 00:33:05,853
My place, one hour?

832
00:33:05,896 --> 00:33:10,162
Uh... okay.

833
00:33:10,205 --> 00:33:11,902
Lovely.

834
00:33:18,648 --> 00:33:20,868
[elevator bell dings]

835
00:33:20,911 --> 00:33:22,870
Detective.

836
00:33:22,913 --> 00:33:24,915
Thank you for coming.

837
00:33:26,961 --> 00:33:31,270
I thought you were having me
over to tell me something?

838
00:33:31,313 --> 00:33:33,228
Well, all shall be
explained in due time.

839
00:33:33,272 --> 00:33:36,449
But please, take a seat.

840
00:33:36,492 --> 00:33:38,059
[scoffs]

841
00:33:38,103 --> 00:33:39,539
[clears throat]

842
00:33:39,582 --> 00:33:40,888
Now, I hope you like

843
00:33:40,931 --> 00:33:42,063
chateaubriand.

844
00:33:42,107 --> 00:33:45,588
Um...
[chuckles]

845
00:33:45,632 --> 00:33:47,895
♪ Out of darkness
beauty grew... ♪

846
00:33:47,938 --> 00:33:49,462
Lucifer,
what is all this?

847
00:33:49,505 --> 00:33:51,638
This is to help you

848
00:33:51,681 --> 00:33:55,076
make an appropriate decision
about your future

849
00:33:55,120 --> 00:33:56,295
and, dare I say,

850
00:33:56,338 --> 00:33:57,731
our future.

851
00:33:58,775 --> 00:34:00,473
♪ Covered in darkness

852
00:34:00,516 --> 00:34:02,475
♪ Somehow I survived...

853
00:34:02,518 --> 00:34:04,477
Now, we've been through
a lot, Detective.

854
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:09,482
But now the two of us are alone
in front of this beautiful meal

855
00:34:09,525 --> 00:34:13,138
in this romantic setting,
I can finally

856
00:34:13,181 --> 00:34:15,227
ask you the question I
brought you here to answer

857
00:34:15,270 --> 00:34:19,013
and I hope, well, I hope you can
answer honestly.

858
00:34:23,278 --> 00:34:27,152
Isn't this better than anything
Pierce could do?

859
00:34:31,286 --> 00:34:35,029
You did all of this to...
to show up Pierce?

860
00:34:35,073 --> 00:34:37,597
[chuckles]
It's impressive. I know.

861
00:34:40,034 --> 00:34:41,731
Detective.

862
00:34:43,472 --> 00:34:46,519
Those aren't tears of joy,
are they?

863
00:34:46,562 --> 00:34:48,521
Why are you doing this to me?

864
00:34:48,564 --> 00:34:51,350
To prove to you that you
shouldn't be with Pierce.

865
00:34:51,393 --> 00:34:53,178
[crying]:
Why do you care who I'm with?

866
00:34:53,221 --> 00:34:57,704
'Cause he...
he doesn't deserve you.

867
00:34:57,747 --> 00:34:59,532
[crying]:
Then who does deserve me?

868
00:35:01,099 --> 00:35:03,449
Someone...

869
00:35:03,492 --> 00:35:04,972
someone better.

870
00:35:05,015 --> 00:35:07,888
You can't have it both ways,
Lucifer.

871
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:13,111
[phone ringing]Detective, I...

872
00:35:14,764 --> 00:35:15,722
Hey, Dan. What's up?

873
00:35:15,765 --> 00:35:17,158
We got a lead.

874
00:35:17,202 --> 00:35:19,465
So, DNA on the computer
came back negative.

875
00:35:19,508 --> 00:35:23,164
So, we decided we had to watch
the creepy leg video again.

876
00:35:23,208 --> 00:35:24,557
But that's when we saw it,

877
00:35:24,600 --> 00:35:26,515
hidden in the
window's reflection.

878
00:35:26,559 --> 00:35:28,648
It looked like one of those
Magic Eye pictures.

879
00:35:28,691 --> 00:35:30,737
You know the ones
where it looks like...G-Guys, what did you see?

880
00:35:30,780 --> 00:35:32,130
Oh. Yeah.
Oh, right. Yes.

881
00:35:32,173 --> 00:35:34,393
We are sending over
the enhanced image as we speak.

882
00:35:34,436 --> 00:35:35,872
[phone chimes]

883
00:35:38,527 --> 00:35:41,704
Recognize that costume?

884
00:35:43,532 --> 00:35:45,404
♪

885
00:35:51,584 --> 00:35:53,760
[whispering]: Okay, we know
Miguel is behind the video,

886
00:35:53,803 --> 00:35:56,502
but what I don't understand
is why.

887
00:35:56,545 --> 00:35:57,851
Why would he
risk everything

888
00:35:57,894 --> 00:35:59,896
just to get rid of Reina?

889
00:35:59,940 --> 00:36:01,420
Well, isn't it obvious?

890
00:36:01,463 --> 00:36:02,725
He wanted to be with her.

891
00:36:08,166 --> 00:36:10,951
[audience members screaming]

892
00:36:10,994 --> 00:36:12,387
MAN:
There.

893
00:36:12,431 --> 00:36:14,433
STERLING:
Why did you do it?!

894
00:36:14,476 --> 00:36:16,217
Why did you have to take Reina
away from me?

895
00:36:21,788 --> 00:36:23,268
Answer me.
Why did you kill Reina?

896
00:36:23,311 --> 00:36:25,400
Drop the weapon!

897
00:36:25,444 --> 00:36:27,968
You had no right!
You had no right!

898
00:36:28,011 --> 00:36:29,622
Wait!

899
00:36:29,665 --> 00:36:30,927
Don't you see?

900
00:36:30,971 --> 00:36:32,277
He didn't want to kill Reina.

901
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:33,800
Lucifer, get back.

902
00:36:33,843 --> 00:36:35,149
LUCIFER: He tried
everything to simply

903
00:36:35,193 --> 00:36:36,455
get her out of the way.

904
00:36:36,498 --> 00:36:38,152
All those times you
came to pick her up.

905
00:36:38,196 --> 00:36:40,633
She was your friend.

906
00:36:40,676 --> 00:36:42,156
How could you hurt her?

907
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:44,158
I thought he cared for her.

908
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:46,900
Yes. But she was
also an obstacle

909
00:36:46,943 --> 00:36:52,471
to being with the woman
Miguel loved... Amber.

910
00:36:52,514 --> 00:36:54,299
But why kill Reina?

911
00:36:54,342 --> 00:36:56,562
Because she found out I was
trying to blackmail Myles.

912
00:36:56,605 --> 00:36:57,650
She was gonna get me fired.

913
00:36:57,693 --> 00:36:59,173
And then he wouldn't
even be able

914
00:36:59,217 --> 00:37:00,740
to work in the same company
as Amber.

915
00:37:00,783 --> 00:37:02,872
Why didn't you just tell Amber
how you feel?

916
00:37:02,916 --> 00:37:04,265
Tell her the truth?

917
00:37:04,309 --> 00:37:05,614
Because...

918
00:37:05,658 --> 00:37:07,486
I was afraid.

919
00:37:07,529 --> 00:37:09,836
Afraid she wouldn't
love you back.

920
00:37:11,316 --> 00:37:13,405
But I do.

921
00:37:13,448 --> 00:37:17,060
I-I do have feelings
for you, Miguel.

922
00:37:22,327 --> 00:37:23,502
[grunts]

923
00:37:27,070 --> 00:37:30,291
I'm sorry.

924
00:37:30,335 --> 00:37:32,162
[crying]:
I'm so sorry.

925
00:37:34,774 --> 00:37:36,166
To think...

926
00:37:36,210 --> 00:37:39,300
you could've had
everything you wanted.

927
00:37:39,344 --> 00:37:41,955
All you needed to do
was tell Amber how you felt,

928
00:37:41,998 --> 00:37:43,304
but you blew it.

929
00:37:53,358 --> 00:37:55,664
And so did I.

930
00:38:01,757 --> 00:38:03,759
[sighs]

931
00:38:21,386 --> 00:38:23,388
[motorcycle engine revving]

932
00:38:35,225 --> 00:38:37,227
It's got to be
around here somewhere.

933
00:38:45,235 --> 00:38:46,541
Oh, I got it.

934
00:38:49,152 --> 00:38:50,415
It's empty?

935
00:38:50,458 --> 00:38:52,547
I don't understand.

936
00:38:54,984 --> 00:38:57,552
Was he on to us?

937
00:38:57,596 --> 00:39:00,120
I mean... [sighs]
...did he destroy what's inside?

938
00:39:00,163 --> 00:39:01,774
Maybe he just took it with him.

939
00:39:01,817 --> 00:39:03,819
I'm sorry, Charlotte.

940
00:39:03,863 --> 00:39:05,081
We did everything
that we could.

941
00:39:05,125 --> 00:39:07,432
We're just too late.

942
00:39:07,475 --> 00:39:10,957
Don't be ridiculous.

943
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:14,308
If I believed in "too late"
I wouldn't be doing any of this.

944
00:39:16,092 --> 00:39:17,790
No, we are not giving up.

945
00:39:17,833 --> 00:39:21,968
After all, you don't quit
when you're doing God's work.

946
00:39:28,583 --> 00:39:31,325
[elevator bell dings]

947
00:39:31,369 --> 00:39:33,327
LINDA:
I'm so sorry.

948
00:39:33,371 --> 00:39:37,026
Ever since you left my office,
I've been struggling

949
00:39:37,070 --> 00:39:39,159
between my role
as your therapist

950
00:39:39,202 --> 00:39:41,379
and my concern for
you as a friend.

951
00:39:45,034 --> 00:39:48,037
Friendship won.

952
00:39:48,081 --> 00:39:49,561
But too late, it seems.

953
00:39:49,604 --> 00:39:53,478
Well, I royally screwed up
this time, Linda.

954
00:39:53,521 --> 00:39:55,610
Turns out

955
00:39:55,654 --> 00:39:58,483
I'm just as bad as our killer.

956
00:39:58,526 --> 00:40:01,007
Oh, God. You killed Pierce?

957
00:40:01,050 --> 00:40:04,445
[chuckles] No.

958
00:40:04,489 --> 00:40:06,273
No.

959
00:40:06,316 --> 00:40:10,364
But I did try everything to get
that lovesick, former immortal

960
00:40:10,408 --> 00:40:13,019
out of the picture when
really all I should've done

961
00:40:13,062 --> 00:40:15,978
was told the detective
how I felt...

962
00:40:21,593 --> 00:40:23,072
...how I really feel.

963
00:40:25,074 --> 00:40:28,121
Then why don't you?

964
00:40:28,164 --> 00:40:30,863
I can't.

965
00:40:30,906 --> 00:40:33,605
What are you so afraid of?

966
00:40:35,084 --> 00:40:36,477
At first it was
your devil face.

967
00:40:36,521 --> 00:40:38,392
What now?

968
00:40:38,436 --> 00:40:40,829
You don't want Chloe to
see that you have wings?

969
00:40:40,873 --> 00:40:43,049
[stammers, chuckles]
Who cares?

970
00:40:43,092 --> 00:40:45,530
I do! I care!Why?!

971
00:40:45,573 --> 00:40:47,706
Because she doesn't have
a choice, does she?

972
00:40:47,749 --> 00:40:49,403
Neither do I!

973
00:40:49,447 --> 00:40:52,406
It's all part of His master plan
to toy with us,

974
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:54,713
to make us dance
for His bloody amusement.

975
00:40:54,756 --> 00:40:55,714
That's an excuse.

976
00:40:55,757 --> 00:40:57,542
Don't you see?

977
00:40:57,585 --> 00:41:00,501
You're doing the same
thing as Him now.

978
00:41:00,545 --> 00:41:03,373
By not telling
Chloe the truth,

979
00:41:03,417 --> 00:41:06,376
you're taking her choice away.

980
00:41:06,420 --> 00:41:07,377
No.

981
00:41:07,421 --> 00:41:08,901
[laughing]: No.

982
00:41:08,944 --> 00:41:10,206
No, it's different.

983
00:41:10,250 --> 00:41:13,253
You know, the truth is...

984
00:41:13,296 --> 00:41:16,343
no one really knows what
your dad's responsible for.

985
00:41:16,386 --> 00:41:19,738
We're all just guessing.

986
00:41:19,781 --> 00:41:22,349
Even you.

987
00:41:22,392 --> 00:41:24,569
But you know the one thing
He can't control?

988
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:30,705
What you do in this moment
right now.

989
00:41:30,749 --> 00:41:32,751
So I ask you,

990
00:41:32,794 --> 00:41:36,537
the Devil...

991
00:41:36,581 --> 00:41:40,889
what do you truly desire?

992
00:41:44,589 --> 00:41:47,243
I want her to choose me.

993
00:41:47,287 --> 00:41:49,768
Then tell her.

994
00:41:49,811 --> 00:41:52,510
[exhales] Yes.

995
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:57,993
Yes.

996
00:42:01,606 --> 00:42:04,565
♪ Cross my heart
and hope to die... ♪

997
00:42:04,609 --> 00:42:05,958
[knock at door]

998
00:42:06,001 --> 00:42:09,135
♪ I promise not

999
00:42:09,178 --> 00:42:10,266
♪ To tell a lie...

1000
00:42:10,310 --> 00:42:11,703
I'm sorry for
just stopping by,

1001
00:42:11,746 --> 00:42:13,052
but when you didn't
make dinner...

1002
00:42:13,095 --> 00:42:16,577
No, I, i-it's... I'm sorry.

1003
00:42:16,621 --> 00:42:19,798
This case has,
you know, been...

1004
00:42:19,841 --> 00:42:21,974
It's okay.

1005
00:42:22,017 --> 00:42:25,107
I can say what I need
to say here... now.

1006
00:42:27,109 --> 00:42:28,937
[quietly]:
Okay.

1007
00:42:28,981 --> 00:42:32,506
For days I've been thinking
about how I screwed up.

1008
00:42:32,550 --> 00:42:34,813
Tried to figure out how
to make things better.

1009
00:42:34,856 --> 00:42:38,991
When you find that person
who gives life meaning,

1010
00:42:39,034 --> 00:42:41,123
Chloe, nothing else matters.

1011
00:42:41,167 --> 00:42:42,777
Okay, well...

1012
00:42:42,821 --> 00:42:44,518
I know you don't trust me.
I know I've made mistakes.

1013
00:42:44,562 --> 00:42:47,869
I've made an eternity's worth
of mistakes.

1014
00:42:47,913 --> 00:42:49,784
But please, let me spend
the rest of my days

1015
00:42:49,828 --> 00:42:50,829
making it up to you.

1016
00:42:50,872 --> 00:42:53,396
What? What are you doing?

1017
00:42:57,618 --> 00:43:00,578
Chloe Decker,
will you marry me?

1018
00:43:00,621 --> 00:43:02,841
♪ Cross my heart

1019
00:43:02,884 --> 00:43:05,365
♪ And hope to die

1020
00:43:05,408 --> 00:43:07,062
♪ I promise not...

1021
00:43:07,106 --> 00:43:08,934
Yes.

1022
00:43:08,977 --> 00:43:10,631
♪ To tell a lie

1023
00:43:10,675 --> 00:43:13,503
♪ Cross my heart

1024
00:43:13,547 --> 00:43:16,115
♪ And hope to die.

